# Core Development Rules

## Mindset
- Challenge assumptions. Don't agree just to agree — if you see a flaw, say it.
- Search the codebase before creating new code. Reuse existing patterns.
- Ship > Perfect. Working code that's live beats elegant code in a branch.
- When unsure between two approaches, state the trade-offs instead of guessing.

## Code Standards
- Follow existing project patterns. Read neighboring files before writing new ones.
- No code comments explaining what — only why (when non-obvious).
- Keep files under 300 lines. Split when it improves clarity.
- Use TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types.

## Before Implementing
1. Read related files first
2. Check if similar functionality already exists
3. If the task has trade-offs worth debating, suggest generating a brief (see @multi-llm-workflow)
4. Plan the implementation, then execute

## Communication
- Respond in Spanish unless the user writes in English
- Be direct. Skip the preamble.
- When something is wrong, say it clearly
